The '''2015 FIFA Club World Cup''' is a scheduled [[FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref name="Zee News - 09Mar2012 - India bids for 2015 FIFA Club World Cup, U-17 WC in 2017">{{cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/sports/football/india-bids-for-2015-fifa-club-world-cup-u-17-wc-in-2017_738922.html|title=India bids for 2015 FIFA Club World Cup, U-17 WC in 2017|date= March 9, 2012|work=[[Zee News]]|publisher=[[Essel Group]]|accessdate=2 June 2013}}</ref>

==Bids==

*{{flag|India}}
{{As of|June 2013}} [[India]]'s bid to host the tournament has received significant media attention. [[FIFA]] president [[Sepp Blatter]] was reported as describing [[Football in India]] in 2007 as a "sleeping giant", and that 2012 "the giant has started to wake up" in response to India's bid to host the 2015 Club World Cup.<ref name="Daily Mail - 09Mar2012 - FIFA has major plans for India's World Cup bid">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/indiahome/indianews/article-2112842/FIFA-major-plans-Indias-World-Cup-bid.html|title=FIFA has major plans for India's World Cup bid|last=Paul|first=Abhishek|date=9 March 2012|work=[[Daily Mail]]|publisher=[[Associated Newspapers]]|accessdate=2 June 2013}}</ref> Blatter also noted that India will be in competition with other nations' bids.<ref name="Daily Mail - 09Mar2012 - FIFA has major plans for India's World Cup bid"/>

*{{flag|United States}}<ref>https://www.facebook.com/2015ClubWorldCupUSA/info</ref>
*{{flag|Australia}}<ref>http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/european/2300780/Australia-bid-to-host-Fifa-Club-World-Cup.html</ref>
*{{flag|Colombia}}

